.TH "drm_property_create_enum" 9 "drm_property_create_enum" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_property_create_enum \- create a new enumeration property type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_property *" drm_property_create_enum
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_prop_enum_list *props "  ","
.BI "int num_values "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
drm device
.IP "flags" 12
flags specifying the property type
.IP "name" 12
name of the property
.IP "props" 12
enumeration lists with property values
.IP "num_values" 12
number of pre-defined values
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This creates a new generic drm property which can then be attached to a drm
object with \fBdrm_object_attach_property\fP. The returned property object must
be freed with \fBdrm_property_destroy\fP, which is done automatically when
calling \fBdrm_mode_config_cleanup\fP.

Userspace is only allowed to set one of the predefined values for enumeration
properties.
.SH "RETURN"
A pointer to the newly created property on success, NULL on failure.
